===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|し|yomi=o}}
From {{bor|ja|ltc|-}} {{ltc-l|肆}}.

The numeral sense is a substitute spelling for {{ja-r|四|し|[[four]]}}, likely borrowed from similar usage of written {{der|ja|zh|肆|tr=-||[[four]]}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|し|acc=1}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|し}}

# {{lb|ja|financial|archaic|sort=し}} the number [[four]], [[4]] {{q|used only in legal documents, otherwise {{m|ja|四}}}}

=====Usage notes=====
Legal uses arose due to the relative ease with which certain number kanji can be fraudulently altered to look like other number kanji.  For instance, {{m|ja|二|tr=ni||two}} could be modified to look like {{m|ja|四|tr=shi||four}}, but it cannot be modified to look like {{m|ja|肆|tr=shi||four|pos=in legal contexts}}.

